  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubFantasy0001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A thick, ochre tonic distilled from giant-thistle root and a measured drop of frost-giant marrow. The flask hums faintly when uncorked and the first swallow tastes of cold iron. Brewed by alchemists who insist the recipe is heirloom; competitors insist it is luck.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 10 minutes you have a +2 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks and advantage on Strength saving throws made to resist being grappled, shoved, or restrained.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Giantsbreath Tonic (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Giantsbreath Tonic.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) checks (your hands feel oversized and clumsy).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 4.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(4 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Tincture Dropper.</em></p>"
    },
